         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div  type="translation" source="#oliverioDAI" xml:lang="it"><p>M. Aurelio Flaviano, Valeria Marciana il dilettissimo figlio (suo, ha onorato). 
               D(ecreto - <hi rend="italic">per decreto</hi> - del) S(enato)</p></div>
            <div type="translation" source="#edd" xml:lang="en"><p>M(arcus) Aurelius Flavianus: Valeria Marciana <supplied reason="subaudible">honoured</supplied> her 
            dearest son. By Decree of the Council.</p></div>
         </div>
         
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>For the statue which probably stood on the base see <bibl><ptr target="rosenbaum1960"/>, no. 116</bibl>, Brinkerhoff in <bibl><ptr target="kraeling1962"/>
               p. 184, p. 204 , no. 63.</bibl></p>
            <p>Apparently a pair with <ref type="inscription">P17500</ref>; there is however no indication in the nomenclature of a direct family relationship, suggested by Brinkerhoff.</p>
            <p>The name probably indicates a date in the late second or early third century.
               <!-- there is no basis in the nomenclature for Brinkerhoff's suggestion that he was a
                    relation of Marcus Antonius Flavianus, p. 181, lines 4, 5. --> </p>
            <!-- <p>For civic organisation at Ptolemais see Introduction XXX</p> -->
         </div>
         
